#PyPassword Generator (Python)

A simple Python program that generates a randomized password using letters, numbers, and symbols.
You can choose how many of each type you want.


#Features

Random letters (A–Z, a–z)

Random numbers (0–9)

Random symbols (!, #, $, %, &, etc.)

Password order is fully shuffled

User decides the number of characters

Clean and simple code structure


#How It Works

Run the program

Input:

Number of letters

Number of symbols

Number of numbers

The program:

Randomly selects characters

Shuffles the order

Prints the final password


